The State moves to withdraw the Information and to amend the charge to fraudulent use of credit card, contrary to Section 943.41(5)1a  of the Wisconsin Statutes.  Motion granted.
The State if to file an Amended complaint.
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge. Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) Months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Maintain fulltime employment/schooling/work search;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
4) pay a $250.00 fine plus costs, total of $568.00.
Minutes.
